"title": "7719: elders, as community leaders",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7719: elders, as community leaders",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Since older men act as responsible leaders in many communities, “elder” is used as the title for a recognised leader.</p>\n<h2>Elders in early Israel</h2>\n<h3>Elders represented their people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:7\">EXO 19:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:16\">EXO 3:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:29\">EXO 4:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:21-Exod12:28\">EXO 12:21–12:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:1\">EXO 24:1</a></p>\n<h3>Elders assisted Moses</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:16-Num11:17\">NUM 11:16–11:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod18:21-Exod18:26\">EXO 18:21–18:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:24-Num11:25\">NUM 11:24–11:25</a></p>\n<h3>Elders met in a national assembly</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh23:2\">JOS 23:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh24:1\">JOS 24:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg21:16\">JDG 21:16</a></p>\n<h3>Elders functioned as judges, sometimes in the town gate</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut19:11-Deut19:12\">DEU 19:11–19:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg8:14\">JDG 8:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth4:1-Ruth4:12\">RUT 4:1–4:12</a></p>\n<h2>Elders during the period of the monarchy</h2>\n<h3>Tribal and town elders</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam30:26-1Sam30:31\">1SA 30:26–30:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs10:5\">2KI 10:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:1\">2KI 23:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer19:1\">JER 19:1</a></p>\n<h3>Elders were local representatives at national functions</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:1\">1KI 8:1</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Elders advised the king</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:6-1Kgs12:8\">1KI 12:6–12:8</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Elders functioned as judges at the town gate</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:23\">PRO 31:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:8-1Kgs21:14\">1KI 21:8–21:14</a></p>\n<h2>Elders in Israel during and after the exile</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra10:8\">EZR 10:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra10:14\">EZR 10:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek8:1\">EZK 8:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek14:1\">EZK 14:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:1-Ezek20:3\">EZK 20:1–20:3</a></p>\n<h2>Elders in NT Jewish society</h2>\n<h3>Elders were local town and synagogue leaders</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:22\">MRK 5:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:1-Luke7:5\">LUK 7:1–7:5</a></p>\n<h3>Elders were members of the Sanhedrin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:1\">MRK 15:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:22\">MAT 5:22</a></p>\n<h3>Elders were guardians of religious traditions</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:1-Matt15:2\">MAT 15:1–15:2</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:5\">MRK 7:5</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:3\">MRK 7:3</a></p>\n<h3>The elders' rejection of Jesus Christ predicted by him</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:21\">MAT 16:21</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:31\">MRK 8:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:22\">LUK 9:22</a></p>\n<h3>The involvement of the elders in the trial and condemnation of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:1\">MAT 27:1</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:1\">MRK 15:1</a></p>\n<h3>The elders' involvement with the first Christians</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:5\">ACT 4:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:8\">ACT 4:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:23\">ACT 4:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:21\">ACT 5:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:12\">ACT 6:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:14\">ACT 23:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts25:15\">ACT 25:15</a></p>",
